  "plot outline": "On 29 June 1613 in London, the Globe Theatre, run by famous playwright William Shakespeare, accidentally burns to the ground. Seriously affected, he stops writing and returns to his hometown, where his wife Anne and daughters Judith and Susanna are surprised to hear that he intends to stay there definitively, after two decades working in the capital, neglecting his sincere affections for them.",
